From: Zhihao Cheng <chengzhihao1@huawei.com>
Date: Tue, 10 May 2022 20:31:26 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] ubi: ubi_create_volume: Fix use-after-free when volume
 creation failed
Git-commit: 8c03a1c21d72210f81cb369cc528e3fde4b45411
Patch-mainline: v5.19-rc1
References: CVE-2022-49388 bsc#1237934

There is an use-after-free problem for 'eba_tbl' in ubi_create_volume()'s
error handling path:

  ubi_eba_replace_table(vol, eba_tbl)
    vol->eba_tbl = tbl
Out_mapping: ubi_eba_destroy_table(eba_tbl)   // Free 'eba_tbl'
Out_unlock: put_device(&vol->dev)
    vol_release
      kfree(tbl->entries)	  // UAF

Fix it by removing redundant 'eba_tbl' releasing.
Fetch a reproducer in [Link].

Fixes: 493cfaeaa0c9b ("mtd: utilize new cdev_device_add helper function")
Link: https://bugzilla.kernel.org/show_bug.cgi?id=215965
Signed-off-by: Zhihao Cheng <chengzhihao1@huawei.com>
Signed-off-by: Richard Weinberger <richard@nod.at>
Signed-off-by: David Sterba <dsterba@suse.com>
---
 drivers/mtd/ubi/vmt.c |    1 -
 1 file changed, 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/mtd/ubi/vmt.c
+++ b/drivers/mtd/ubi/vmt.c
@@ -314,7 +314,6 @@ out_mapping:
 	ubi->volumes[vol_id] = NULL;
 	ubi->vol_count -= 1;
 	spin_unlock(&ubi->volumes_lock);
-	ubi_eba_destroy_table(eba_tbl);
 out_acc:
 	spin_lock(&ubi->volumes_lock);
 	ubi->rsvd_pebs -= vol->reserved_pebs;
